#### Exit status###

1. Every time a command is executed it returns an exist status
2. Range from 0 to 255
3. 0 = success else error
4. use man or info to find meaning of exit status 

$? contains the return code of the previously executed command
example: 
   ls /not/there 
   echo "$?"

   output 2
   
   ### you sehll script also returns an exit command, you can control the status code by using the following statement 
   exit 0 
   by default it is the resuklt of last comand executed
   exit status stops the excecution of the script